SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 29-39-102(h), is amended by adding
the following as a new subdivision:
(5)
(A) If the defendant violated § 63-6-1103(b) by sending an abortion-
inducing drug, as defined in § 63-6-1102, into this state to a patient via courier,
delivery, or mail service. Notwithstanding another law to the contrary, any such
defendant is strictly liable to the patient, or other wrongful death beneficiary
under § 20-5-106(a), in the statutory amount of five million dollars ($5,000,000) in
compensatory damages for the wrongful death of a person, as defined in § 20-5-
106(d), caused by the abortion-inducing drug.
(B) This subdivision (h)(5) does not apply to:
(i) A pharmacist, as defined in § 63-10-204;
(ii) A physician, as defined in § 63-6-1102;
(iii) A motor carrier or freight forwarder, as defined in 49 U.S.C. §
13102; or
(iv) An air carrier, as defined in 49 U.S.C. § 40102.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 29-39-102(m), is amended by
deleting the subsection and substituting:
